The list() function

The list() function can transform a series of subsequent generator invocations into a real list:

def powers_of_2(n):
    power = 1
    for i in range(n):
        yield power
        power *= 2
 
 
t = list(powers_of_2(3))
print(t)

PS D:\Phyton> & C:/Users/gl634/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python313/python.exe "d:/Phyton/Cisco Phyton/generator.py"
[1, 2, 4]
